": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 5, "created_at": "2019-11-05T21:19:55Z", "updated_at": "2019-11-18T14:55:51Z", "closed_at": "2019-11-18T14:55:50Z", "author_association": "COLLABORATOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "I'm extending my Tornado handlers to use decorators specifying a schema that they expect. ie.\r\n\r\n```python\r\nclass MyHandler(RequestHandler):\r\n    @expects(body=UserSchema())\r\n    async def put(self, body, user_id):\r\n    \"\"\"<apispec docstring>\"\"\"\r\n    ...\r\n```\r\nmy `expects` decorator reads the request body, validates it according to the schema and then gives it to the method. Any parameters from the path are still function arguments, in this case `user_id`.\r\n\r\nHowever, this alters the method signature which currently breaks the `TornadoPlugin.tornadopath2openapi` helper as this helper uses `inspect.signature` on the method to determine parameter names.\r\n\r\nI'm creating a PR that allows changing the method signature when the `URLSpec` uses named regex groups. Instead of inspecting the method's signature, it first tries to read the `Matcher.regex` to determine parameter names.\r\n\r\n\r\nNote: I'm not supplying any decorators, I just don't want the `TornadoPlugin` to break.", "performed_via_github_app": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/marshmallow-code/apispec-webframeworks/issues/59", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/marshmallow-code/apispec-webframeworks", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/marshmallow-code/apispec-webframeworks/issues/59/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/marshmallow-code/apispec-webframeworks/issues/59/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/marshmallow-code/apispec-webframeworks/issues/59/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/marshmallow-code/apispec-webframeworks/issues/59", "id": 495593330, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU0OTU1OTMzMzA=", "number": 59, "title": "Failed to integrate apispe